cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CVPR

The paper deals with 3D object detection in autonomous driving and robotics, which falls under the intersection of computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper proposes a novel neural network framework for this task, which involves adaptive zooming and learning part locations, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on a popular dataset used in computer vision and robotics research, KITTI, which is often used in the computer vision and pattern recognition conference (cs.CVPR).
